{"id": 5636, "title": "Ticket #5636: Python ExprTrees should cast cleanly to int/float", "description": "<blockquote>\nIn python, expressions can't be cast cleanly to <code>int</code>; the following throws an exception:\n<div class=\"code\">\n<pre class=\"code\">int(classad.ExprTree(\"1+3\"))\n</pre></div>\n\nHowever, we can implement <code>__int__</code> in the <code>ExprTree</code> class and at least try the cast (i.e., we'll still throw when this evaluates to <code>Undefined</code>).\n\n<p>Same story, different verse for <code>float</code>.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Jun-01 08:20</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/aa35b07867c84d2381e2bec7956c6ecc0610fec8\">[48459]</a></span>: (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5636\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5636'); return false;\" title=\"Python ExprTrees should cast cleanly to int/float\">#5636</a></span>) Documentation for casting python <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ExprTree\" title=\"Expr Tree\">ExprTree</a></span> to int or float.  (By Tim Theisen )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2016-Apr-18 20:53</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/61739ff03f50ea3ace3296504a798caaac32b46f\">[48230]</a></span>: Allow casts to int and float. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5636\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5636'); return false;\" title=\"Python ExprTrees should cast cleanly to int/float\">#5636</a></span> When a user tries to cast an expression to an int or float - as in float(classad.ExprTree(\"1234\")) we now \"do the right thing\" instead of raising an exception.  (By Brian )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2016-Jun-01 08:22", "status": "resolved", "created": "2016-Apr-18 14:37", "fixed_version": "2016-Apr-18 14:37", "broken_version": "", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Tools", "assigned_to": "tim", "derived_from": "", "creator": "bbockelm", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "bbockelm@cse.unl.edu", "due_date": ""}